______LINUX_INSTALLATION(UBUNTU)________

sudo yum update -y 
sudo yum installation docker -y 
sudo service docker start 


__________COMMANDS FOR DOCKER_______________

DOCKER PULL IMAGE_NAME ( DOWNLOAD IMAGE FROM THE DOCKER HUB )
DOCKER IMAGE (LIST ALL THE DOCKER IMAGES)
DOCKER RMI ( REMOVE THE DOCKER IMAGE)
DOCKER BUILD -T IMAGE_NAME ( BUILD NEW IMAGE FROM DOCKER FILE )
DOCKER RUN IMAGE_NAME ( CREATE AND START NEW COTANER )
DOCKER PS ( LIST ALL RUNNING CONTAINERS )
DOCKER PS -A ( LIST ALL THE CONTAINER EVEN IF IT'S IS STOPPED )
DOCKER STOP CONTAINER_ID ( STOP THE RUNNING CONATAINER)
DOCKER  START CONTAINER_ID ( START THE CONTAINER)
DOCKER RM ( REMOVE THE CONTAINER FROM THE SYSTEM )
DOCKER LOGS CONTAINER_ID ( VIEW THE LOG FILES )
DOCKER --HELP ( LIST ALL THE AVAILABLE COMMANDS )
